rooms.name: Holme Ave
rooms.description: A wide split highway stretches before you, the greenery in the center island mostly overtaken by weeds and garbage. At its east end, it expands into a large traffic circle with an exit to Welsh Road to the south. There are other exits, but they look less inviting than the rest of this place. The pavement, while cracked and faded, is not entirely hostile. There are people in this region, and they seem to be making a passing effort at upkeeping it. Near the west end of the road, a small house stands partially caved in. The north of the road is lined by overgrown, decaying, inaccessible buildings

transitionEvent.description: Holme Ave is quiet. It's an edge boundary of an entire quiet region.

rooms.name: Welsh Rd
rooms.description: Welsh Road marks the eastern edge of the region, its cracked pavement flanked by silent woods. You get the feeling of being watched when standing out here. To the north, Holme lies still, its emptiness heavy under a gray sky. To the south, Colfax stretches into shadow, its fractured streets offering little comfort. At the center, there is access to the Ruins and to Immaculate East.

transitionEvent.description: Clouds shift, offering an unsettling view of the green palor of the sky.

rooms.name: Immaculate East
rooms.description: This narrow road once served as the entrance and parking lot for a healthcare facility. it still has access to these Ruins.

transitionEvent.description: Threads of conversation carry over on the wind, but you can't make out any words.

rooms.name: Immacualte West
rooms.description: Once a narrow service road connecting the church to the healthcare facility, the quiet sense of this area having been forgotten is especially present here. Trees crowd you, but thankfully the steeple blots out some of the sickly palor of the sky

transitionEvent.description: Sounds are muffled, and the sky seems smaller somehow.

rooms.name: Ruins
rooms.description: The Immaculate Mary Center lies in ruins, its walls cracked and windows shattered. Once a place of healing, it now harbors only remnants of the pastâ€”and dangers lurking in the shadows, waiting for the unwary.

transitionEvent.description: You step into the decaying remains of the Immaculate Mary Center, where silence and decay hide untold dangers in the crumbling halls.

rooms.name: Abandoned Living Room
rooms.description: A musty living room, dim light streaking in from the outside, with the same ever-present green hue. The place is long abandoned, but there is evidence of squatters having been here recently. Along the east wall is a small galley kitchen. The remains of stairs leading to a basement have been rendered unuseable by the partially colapsed roof.

transitionEvent.description: As you enter the room rats and vermin scatter ahead of you, disturbed by your presence.

rooms.name: Abandoned Bathroom
rooms.description: The bathroom of this long abandoned place largely matches the rest of it. So far removed from the days when it served its purpose, and with no water to speak of, this is just another stagnant room with little in it but scrap.

transitionEvent.description: You hear a thump in the distance.

rooms.name: Abandoned Bedroom
rooms.description: Motes of dust hang in the air in a way which, if cast in a more pleasant color, would give this place a sense of peace and quiet. As it is, things just seem forgotten.

rooms.name: Abandoned Closet
rooms.description: The closet still has a bar running its length at about eye level, but nothing hangs on it. Some floorboards are visible around the carpet

transitionEvent.description: What are you doing in here?

rooms.name: Stamford Rd
rooms.description: There is more activity visible around here. Some trees line the streets, a few people pass back and forth among them. To the east is the school, and to the west among the houses is the safe zone.

transitionEvent.description: Seeing these faces makes you more hopeful than afraid, but there is still danger here.

rooms.name: Convent
rooms.denialMessage: Skogsra materializes in front of you as you approach the thick metal doors to the convent, her eyes dark and partially obscured by her dark coif. There are no words exchanged here. A chill runs down your back as you turn, away from her, the convent, and whatever it contains. As you step away, you hear a warning from behind you: "Don't try again. Some places are simply not for you."

rooms.name: Convent Road
rooms.description: A twisting road lined with parking spaces, some occupied by cars. With access to the church and main parking lot, this road sees heavy foot traffic for the area. At its end is the convent: a foreboding structure with a heavy steel door.

rooms.name: Safe Zone
rooms.description: The main floor of one half of a semi-detatched townhome. There's some furniture left, but there is no one else here. A large bay window in the kitchen allows greenish light to spill in, with the living room at the opposite end of the floor cast in darker shadow. The sound of rodents is evident in the walls, but their presence can't be seen.

rooms.name: Safe Zone Closet
rooms.description: The mirrored and cracked paneling on the itnerior of this closet is disorienting and for reasons you can't explain, extends onto the floor.

transitionEvent.description: The mirroring disorients you as you look around and see yourself cast at odd angles by the intersecting mirrors.
